          "text": "Done with the service-role refactor. Summary of what changed:\n\n- **db.py**: dropped the anon `supabase` global. Added `supabase_admin` (service role, bypasses RLS) and `get_anon_client()` (throwaway for session-mutating GoTrue calls).\n- **auth.py**: every `device_codes` insert/select/update/delete now goes through `supabase_admin`; `auth.get_user()` does too. `_refresh` uses a fresh throwaway client so its session leak can no longer poison anything.\n- **main.py**: health check uses `supabase_admin`.\n\nNet effect: no long-lived client ever has its session mutated, so `PGRST303: JWT expired` from this code path can't recur.\n\n---\n\n**Other things I noticed that look broken or fragile:**\n\n1. **`.env` `BASE_URL` is missing the scheme.** `BASE_URL=git-ai-production.up.railway.app` — auth.py:85 builds `verification_uri = f\"{BASE_URL}/device\"`, which becomes `git-ai-production.up.railway.app/device`. The CLI (or browser) won't treat that as an absolute URL. Should be `https://git-ai-production.up.railway.app`.\n\n2. **`global_exception_handler` leaks internals.** main.py:38 returns `str(exc)` to the client. Stack-trace-flavored strings, DB error details, and raw library messages all go to whoever calls the API. Log it, return a generic message.\n\n3. **Metrics fallback reports the wrong index.** main.py:172-176 — when the batch insert fails and you retry one-by-one, the inner loop reports `index=j` where `j` is the position in `rows`. But events with invalid `event_id` were skipped earlier, so `j` ≠ original event index whenever any event was rejected. The client gets a misleading offset.\n\n4. **Redundant index in schema.** schema.sql:58 — `idx_device_codes_user_code` duplicates the index Postgres already creates for the `unique` constraint on `user_code`. Harmless, but pure noise.\n\n5. **No RLS policies on any of these tables (based on schema.sql).** If RLS is left disabled, the anon-key-scoped `get_authenticated_client` provides no protection — any logged-in user could read/write any row in `cas_objects` / `metrics_events`. Worth confirming what's actually configured in the Supabase dashboard. With `user_id` columns already in place, the natural policies are `auth.uid() = user_id`.\n\nWant me to fix any of these? And per CLAUDE.md — should I write up the auth refactor in `documentation/git-ai-research-branch-changes.md`?",
